      section.interesting
        .wrapper 
          h3.title Interesting facts
          p.title_p Most American alligators live in Florida and Louisiana. In Florida alone, their number is 1 million individuals.Florida is the only place on Earth where alligators and real crocodiles coexist.
          .acordeon
            .acordeon_title 
              p Species population
              h4.hide _
            .acordeon_description 
              p.desc A total of 60 giant panda cubs were born in 2019, bringing the total population of these animals in captivity around the world to 600. And in the wild there are less than 2,000 giant pandas left. They mainly live in Sichuan and Shaanxi provinces. This animal is not only a symbol of the Celestial Empire, but is also under the protection of the Chinese authorities. Harming a panda is punished very severely.
            .acordeon_title 
              p Region of habitat
              h4.hide _
            .acordeon_description 
              p.desc There are only two countries in the world where representatives of this genus live - these are the United States of America and China. The Chinese alligator is endangered and lives only in the Yangtze River Valley.The American alligator lives on the east coast of the United States from North Carolina to Texas.
            .acordeon_title 
              p Nutrition
              h4.hide _
            .acordeon_description 
              p.desc Alligators feed on almost anything they can catch. Juveniles prey on fish, insects, snails and crustaceans. As they grow, Mississippi alligators choose larger prey: large fish, such as carapace pike (Lepisosteidae); turtles, small mammals, birds and other reptiles, while Chinese alligators, due to their small size, still consume a large number of very small animals. Foreign bodies are often found in the stomachs of alligators. If alligators are hungry enough, they can eat carrion as well. Adult Mississippi alligators can sometimes hunt deer, feral pigs, or even younger alligators, although they are much inferior to most true crocodiles and black caimans for capturing large prey.
              
